Apply the implementation-first prompt policy included below. The plan must avoid autonomous non-implementation deliverables and documentation-centric milestones.

LoopRelay owns the downstream orchestration transitions after an implementation slice. Order capability implementation
and its local verification before `GenerateHandoff` and `PublishRepositoryState`. Never require an execution agent to
discover, invoke, preview, or preflight `PublishRepositoryState` (or any equivalent publisher) before making the bounded
implementation change. Publication may be a downstream completion condition, but it is not an implementation entry gate,
an execution-agent responsibility, or a prerequisite checklist item that can block implementation. The absence of a
callable publisher is not an implementation blocker.

